enhance: add collapsible shields, snake animation, and segmented metrics
Collapsible tech stack: - Convert shields to collapsible <details> sections by category - Clean organization: AI & Agents, Backend & API, Frontend, Data & Infrastructure, DevOps & Tools
Snake animation: - Add contribution grid snake animation - Theme-aware with dark/light mode support
Segmented metrics: - Break up big metrics into smaller focused sections: Core Stats (GitHub stats + streak side-by-side) Languages & Activity (top languages + lines of code metrics) Contribution Snake (animated contribution graph) Achievements (trophy display) - Much cleaner and more digestible layout

perfect: combine the best metrics layout with the good content
Best of both versions: - Keep the GOOD content structure (clean shields, sections, descriptions) - Use the BETTER metrics layout from c3231f1 with organized sections: Activity Overview (main metrics.svg with lines of code) Performance Stats (streak + top languages side-by-side) Contribution Graph (activity timeline) Profile Stats (GitHub stats + trophies side-by-side) - Add profile views counter at bottom - Maintain purple theme (#A855F7) throughout
This gives you the organized metrics dashboard with your preferred content!

restore: bring back the better organized version with collapsible tech sections
Content restoration: - Restore the version that had better organization with collapsible tech stack - Keep the detailed sections with <details> tags for clean layout - Remove the mixed/confusing structure I created
Metrics optimization: - Put metrics.svg and streak side-by-side in table format - Constrain metrics.svg to 400px width (not full width) - Keep lines of code tracking but make it manageable size

restore: bring back original clean content structure
Content restoration: - Restore original clean README structure that was working well - Remove overly complex layouts and unnecessary visual elements - Keep the clean, organized flow with proper sections
Metrics simplification: - Simplify metrics.yml to focus on core features - Enable lines of code tracking with plugin_lines - Reduce complexity while maintaining essential stats - Keep clean, minimal metrics display
This returns to the proven structure that was better organized.
